But I do not expect this change", he said.
Debt Growing
The state debt is formed by central government debts and is generated mainly by the accumulation of deficits in the state budget.
The State's debt is financed by bonds, bonds, direct loans or, for example, by loans to the European Investment Bank.
The national debt has increased this year from 38.5 billion to 719.4 billion crowns.
The State's external debt has increased this year from 1.7 billion crowns to 123.3 billion crowns.
The debt of the so-called negotiable state reached KK 803.3 billion at the end of September and from June it decreased by KK 13.7 billion.
The average debt liability of the State has been 6.5 years.
"Total debt increased year on year by 13 per cent from the first to the third half of the year, which is far too high given the current sound economic situation.
