The amount is mainly the deficit in the State budget which will obviously reach CK76 billion this year, instead of the CK91.3 billion originally planned.
The maximum sources foreseen for the Czech Consolidation Agency are CZK 13.3 billion, the reserve of CZK 10 billion for the payment of pensions, the financing of state-owned debt securities for CZK 43 billion and the repayment of the loans of the European Investment Bank of CZK 1.8 billion.
